  "texts": [
    "Llama-2 maintained similar performance in the external validation data set (n=1,000) and was consistently superior to fine-tuned Zephyr (Supplemental Table 5).",
    "Because Llama-2 had the best performance on both zero-shot and ICL approaches, it was selected as EchoGPT and used for the subsequent expert qualitative review.",
    "After replacing the measurement numbers with random numbers, we observed statistically significant (p<0.0001) but minor decreases in BLEU, METEOR, ROUGE-L, BERT, and RadGraph F1 scores.",
    "One can see that in the provided examples, the report with random numbers doesn't make clinical sense when compared to the original content (Table 5).",
    "We observed fair agreement for conciseness and correctness, moderate agreement for completeness, and good agreement for clinical utility (Table 6)."
  ]
}